Project Summary – Notion RAG Sandbox
We will build a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) system that uses documents stored in a Notion database as the knowledge base.

Data Source
The documents are stored in a Notion database accessed through the Notion API.
1st column (Page type) → contains the document content.
Remaining columns (2nd–last) → contain metadata such as industry, document type, etc.

Vector Storage
Document chunks will be converted into embeddings and stored in Milvus along with their metadata.

Core Features
1️⃣ Grounded Question Answering
Users can ask questions about the documents.
The system retrieves relevant content and generates answers using an LLM.
The answer must include citations showing which documents were used.

2️⃣ Metadata Filtering
Users can filter results based on metadata fields such as:
industry
document type
Example query:
“Show fintech reports about investment.”

3️⃣ Tool-Based Tasks
The system should support tasks like:
Search → find relevant documents
Refine → narrow search results
Compare → compare information across documents

4️⃣ Evaluation
Use RAGAS to evaluate the quality of the RAG system (retrieval and answer quality).


